abstract_summ: COVID-19 is present in 99.1% of surveyed communities with 99.7% reporting mitigation efforts in effect . Practice volume has dropped by 61.6% since the start of the pandemic with most cancellations being provider initiated . Surgical backlog (58.6%), delayed cancer diagnosis (43.2%) and re-establishing normal care with delayed patient (37.8%) were identified as the top 3 challenges .
